Chief Eunuch Wang.

24
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,333
Right Chancellor
sent someone to urge you again.

25
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:50,900
You're doomed when I get back.

26
00:03:02,940 --> 00:03:03,960
Usually,

27
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,770
people are scrambling

28
00:03:08,620 --> 00:03:09,880
to get

29
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:14,666
this purchasing job.

30
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:18,100
Now that the opportunity has come,

31
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,600
why is no one taking it?

32
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:23,560
Right Chancellor.

33
00:03:24,755 --> 00:03:26,860
White wax is expensive.

34
00:03:27,060 --> 00:03:30,520
Imperial Treasury
disbursed less than it did

35
00:03:31,620 --> 00:03:32,830
in previous purchases

36
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:35,670
by Imperial Household Department.

37
00:03:35,955 --> 00:03:37,340
The money is too little, huh?

38
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,190
You can't make a profit,

39
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:43,020
so you're unwilling to share

40
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,660
His Majesty's burdens.

41
00:03:45,820 --> 00:03:47,390
Sharing the burden for His Majesty

42
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,330
is my duty,

43
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:53,100
but the budget this time

44
00:03:55,820 --> 00:03:57,380
is less than 10%,

45
00:03:58,340 --> 00:03:59,710
which is quite difficult.

46
00:04:03,088 --> 00:04:06,430
I'm incompetent and can't do the job.

47
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,920
Please punish me, Right Chancellor.

48
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,050
What about the rest?

49
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:21,590
Who is willing to take on this job?

50
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:36,110
Step outside Chang'an,

51
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:38,688
and you'll see
countless starving people.

52
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:41,720
You hold golden bowls,

53
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,420
but are picky.

54
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:48,470
If you don't want to eat, don't eat!

55
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:32,460
I

56
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:34,360
want

57
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:37,288
to ask for a reward.

58
00:05:42,088 --> 00:05:43,240
What do you want?

59
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,260
I ask

60
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:50,733
for an opportunity
to relieve your worries.

61
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:51,760
Alright.

62
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:54,870
Fortune is found in danger.

63
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:57,440
Interesting.

64
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,580
Those who know me

65
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:14,266
understand my worries.

66
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:20,580
You can have this opportunity.

67
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,222
Thank you, Right Chancellor.

68
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:35,140
=Episode 29=

69
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:38,355
Attendant Yu.

70
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:40,770
Mr. Li.

71
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:43,890
I can calculate

72
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:45,580
the transport cost again

73
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:48,044
to try to reduce some expenses.

74
00:06:53,570 --> 00:06:54,300
Mr. Li.

75
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:57,490
We work for His Majesty.

76
00:06:58,140 --> 00:06:58,860
First of all,

77
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:00,360
we need to do this job well

78
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,200
and successfully.

79
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:03,770
The rest are just details.

80
00:07:04,980 --> 00:07:06,380
Especially the budget.

81
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,866
You can't limit it to a certain amount.

82
00:07:09,660 --> 00:07:12,380
You should know
that claiming less but spending more

83
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:14,300
is called overspending.

84
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:18,422
- Attendant Yu.
- Attendant Yu.

85
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,280
Claiming more but spending less

86
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,380
is called surplus.

87
00:07:25,466 --> 00:07:27,577
Overspending
is a sign of poor performance.

88
00:07:27,644 --> 00:07:30,600
Having a surplus
is the result of effective planning.

89
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:31,380
Tell me.

90
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:33,380
Our litchi transport job

91
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,010
has a long journey

92
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:37,340
with many uncontrollable factors.

93
00:07:37,580 --> 00:07:38,970
If something goes wrong

94
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:41,160
and the budget is stuck,

95
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:43,040
you'll overspend easily.

96
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:44,820
In the end,

97
00:07:45,622 --> 00:07:47,440
if we need to pay an extra one guan,

98
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:50,190
do you think I should pay for it

99
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:51,950
or you should pay for it?

100
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:54,140
Yes.

101
00:07:55,777 --> 00:07:58,320
We should set aside some
for unexpected spending.

102
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,080
You have experience.

103
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:04,755
I'll report it this way first.

104
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,940
Don't worry. Think about it slowly.

105
00:08:07,466 --> 00:08:08,822
Don't make any mistakes.

106
00:08:19,260 --> 00:08:21,244
We have to leave more budget.

107
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,240
You're right.

108
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:27,850
If this transport method works,

109
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:30,700
we will support it.

110
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:35,050
But Li Shande's plan

111
00:08:35,540 --> 00:08:37,888
has a big drawback.

112
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,190
It's too economical.

113
00:08:40,422 --> 00:08:42,960
This economical method doubles the risk.

114
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:45,860
The transportation

115
00:08:46,190 --> 00:08:48,340
requires not only speed,

116
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:49,740
but also stability.

117
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:54,900
A tired horse is prone to fail.

118
00:08:57,940 --> 00:08:58,980
In my opinion,

119
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:01,540
a post station every 30 km

120
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:02,950
is inappropriate.

121
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:05,180
It can be shortened

122
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:06,950
to a change of rider and horse
every 15 km.

123
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,400
Add more post stations too.

124
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:11,440
This post station

125
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:14,711
also needs a place to stay
and a place to feed the horses.

126
00:09:15,530 --> 00:09:18,740
It needs running water and well water.

127
00:09:19,044 --> 00:09:20,422
Each of these post stations

128
00:09:20,466 --> 00:09:23,800
needs to prepare
at least three good horses.

129
00:09:23,844 --> 00:09:24,933
At least...

130
00:09:27,866 --> 00:09:29,330
Two riders.

131
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:32,900
This post station

132
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:34,520
also needs to build a granary

133
00:09:35,070 --> 00:09:36,380
to store food for several months

134
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:38,860
and two cooks

135
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:41,690
to take turns preparing meals every day.

136
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,250
In case the food isn't fresh one day

137
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,377
and causes a stomachache,

138
00:09:45,422 --> 00:09:47,533
or if the horse
isn't obedient and gets sick,

139
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:48,860
we can still remedy it.

140
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,733
We also need to prepare some medicines

141
00:09:52,020 --> 00:09:53,150
for emergencies.

142
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,360
This budget

143
00:09:55,660 --> 00:09:57,180
will far exceed Li Shande's

144
00:09:57,220 --> 00:09:58,822
previous calculations.

145
00:10:00,980 --> 00:10:02,040
Attendant Yu.

146
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:06,020
If it's done well,

147
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:10,444
it's fine, no matter how much you spend.

148
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:14,190
If things are done badly,

149
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:18,420
it's an offense,
no matter how little you spend.

150
00:10:18,940 --> 00:10:21,711
There's no room for mistake.

151
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:25,430
The transportation budget will probably

152
00:10:25,940 --> 00:10:29,370
have to be multiplied several times

153
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:32,020
to be considered safe.

154
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:34,844
What do you think?

155
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,780
I understand

156
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,300
your concerns.

157
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:49,690
Everyone is seeking stability

158
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:51,266
for the litchi transport.

159
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:53,250
I

160
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:54,970
support you,

161
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,350
but...

162
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:02,340
I don't think

163
00:11:03,380 --> 00:11:04,300
your budget

164
00:11:05,755 --> 00:11:07,450
is safe enough.

165
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:11,080
Why not

166
00:11:13,888 --> 00:11:15,650
multiply it again?

167
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:21,740
When I saw the notebook

168
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:24,111
Li Shande wrote with great effort,

169
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:27,830
I felt sorry for him
for being assigned such a doomed task,

170
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,280
but he completed the job

171
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,300
with clear logic

172
00:11:30,688 --> 00:11:33,520
and perfect efficiency.

173
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:36,400
That made me
eager to help him find a solution.

174
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:37,660
But I didn't expect him

175
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:39,844
to be in cahoots with Attendant Yu.

176
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:42,020
This big-headed fool.

177
00:11:42,020 --> 00:11:43,800
Regardless of whether he's with him,

178
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:44,860
anyone who's related...

179
00:11:48,820 --> 00:11:50,820
Anyone who's related
to this turtle

180
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:52,940
won't end well.

181
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:55,570
This turtle has a big appetite.

182
00:11:56,488 --> 00:11:58,050
The cost of the litchi transport

183
00:11:58,380 --> 00:12:01,360
is probably going to snowball.

184
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:04,860
Although it was a doomed task,

185
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:06,422
it had a chance of survival.

186
00:12:06,940 --> 00:12:08,970
Now that Attendant Yu is involved,

187
00:12:09,866 --> 00:12:13,180
Litchi Envoy has embarked
on a path of no return.

188
00:12:13,688 --> 00:12:15,990
He thought the silver token
that Right Chancellor gave him

189
00:12:16,022 --> 00:12:17,155
would protect him.

190
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,220
He didn't even think

191
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:22,400
about the fact
that he was the litchi transport envoy.

192
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:26,140
If he messes up,

193
00:12:30,133 --> 00:12:32,977
Right Chancellor only needs
to take back the silver token.

194
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:34,440
And there will be no connection

195
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:36,700
between the two of them.

196
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:45,260
You're absolutely right.

197
00:12:45,980 --> 00:12:48,711
Attendant Yu can also protect himself.

198
00:12:50,380 --> 00:12:51,380
Li Shande

199
00:12:51,755 --> 00:12:53,911
arranged today's meeting.

200
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:57,230
Li Shande also
delegated everyone's duties.

201
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,960
Li Shande also led the discussion

202
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:03,420
on the transport method
and its improvement.

203
00:13:05,977 --> 00:13:07,911
The Softshell Turtle On Top already said

204
00:13:09,260 --> 00:13:10,660
he's only responsible for serving

205
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:12,288
and helping everyone solve problems.

206
00:13:12,340 --> 00:13:14,380
His statement is flawlessly worded.

207
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:16,680
If it succeeds,
he'll get all the credit.

208
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:18,420
If it fails,

209
00:13:19,060 --> 00:13:21,977
that's because
Li Shande didn't do a good job.

210
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:34,510
I felt

211
00:13:34,660 --> 00:13:35,860
your support.

212
00:13:36,340 --> 00:13:37,510
I have to travel tomorrow.

213
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:39,020
Really. Please go back.

214
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:45,420
Mr. Li, bravo.

215
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:48,340
- Good.
- Good.

216
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:49,850
Congratulations

217
00:13:50,660 --> 00:13:51,760
on the transport method.

218
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:54,540
We used to get drunk together.

219
00:13:55,555 --> 00:13:57,288
Now, he thrives like a fish in water.

220
00:13:58,660 --> 00:14:00,100
Although he hasn't make it big,

221
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:05,244
things and people have changed.

222
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:10,333
Liangyuan.

223
00:14:11,444 --> 00:14:13,080
Where is your original intention?

224
00:14:14,380 --> 00:14:15,133
Han.

225
00:14:21,380 --> 00:14:22,400
Take care.

226
00:14:31,020 --> 00:14:33,050
You're generous.

227
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,244
When you become successful,
don't forget us.

